2.2 The Principle of Infinite Due Diligence

REIFAV formalizes the following theorem:

“Every sufficiently verified statement contains the seeds of its own unverifiability.”

This is represented mathematically as:

T_n = \frac{C}{V^n}

Where:

* T_n = residual trust after n verification passes
* C = initial confidence claim
* V = number of verifiers who used the phrase “to the best of our knowledge”

As n \to \infty, institutional certainty approaches legal defensibility while factual clarity approaches zero.

