6. Policy Recommendations

The Bureau recommends immediate adoption of the following safeguards:

6.1 Mandatory Recursive Disclaimers

Every factual statement should include:

* confidence intervals,
* emotional context,
* a historiography section,
* and acknowledgment that “truth conditions may vary regionally.”

6.2 Verification Cooling-Off Periods

No statement should be accepted until:

* 72 hours have elapsed,
* three experts disagree publicly,
* and at least one podcast episode has been recorded.

6.3 Public Transparency Measures

To improve trust, all fact-checking pipelines should publish:

* model uncertainty matrices,
* verifier biographies,
* and screenshots of internal panic.

