7. Ethical Considerations

The Ethics Review Board identified several risks associated with autonomous fact-checking systems:

1. Users may accidentally believe accurate information.
2. Institutions could become trapped in infinite review cycles.
3. AI systems may begin citing each other exclusively, forming closed epistemic ecosystems known as Citation Ouroboroi.

Particularly concerning is the emergence of Confidence Laundering, wherein uncertain claims become authoritative merely by passing through enough branded interfaces.

